<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900501-0139</DOCNO><DOCID>900501-0139.</DOCID><HL>   South Korean Exchange Curbs</HL><DATE>05/01/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A14</SO><CO>   FREST</CO><IN>MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)FOREIGN-EXCHANGE MARKETS (FRX)</IN><LP>   SEOUL, South Korea -- The South Korean governmenttoughened foreign exchange controls again, in a move toprevent capital flight and excessive spending by overseastravelers.   The Ministry of Finance said it will no longer permitSouth Koreans to buy up to $5,000 worth of foreign currencyon presentation of their identification cards.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>